def show_images(img, title):
    fig, axes = plot.subplots()
    fig.suptitle(title)
    img = img / 2 + 0.5
    npimg = img.numpy()
    plot.imshow(np.transpose(npimg, (1, 2, 0)), interpolation='nearest', aspect='auto')
    plot.show()

classes = ('plane', 'car', 'bird', 'cat', 'deer',
    'dog', 'frog', 'horse', 'ship', 'truck')

for images, labels in train_data_loader:
    show_images(torchvision.utils.make_grid(images), 'Train samples')
    print(' '.join(f'{classes[labels[j]]:5s}' for j in range(batch_size)))
    break;

for images, labels in train_data_loader:
    show_images(torchvision.utils.make_grid(images), 'Test samples')
    print(' '.join(f'{classes[labels[j]]:5s}' for j in range(batch_size)))
    break;

class ConvolutionalNeuralNetwork(torch.nn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super(ConvolutionalNeuralNetwork, self).__init__()
    #   : 3   , 64  , 3x3   
        self.conv1 = torch.nn.Conv2d(3, 64, 3)
        self.conv2 = torch.nn.Conv2d(64, 128, 3)
        self.conv3 = torch.nn.Conv2d(128, 256, 3)
        self.pool = torch.nn.MaxPool2d(2, 2)
        self.fc1 = torch.nn.Linear(64 * 4 * 4, 128)
        self.fc2 = torch.nn.Linear(128, 256)
        self.fc3 = torch.nn.Linear(256, 10)
    
    def forward(self, x):
        x = self.pool(torch.nn.functional.relu(self.conv1(x)))
        x = self.pool(torch.nn.functional.relu(self.conv2(x)))
        x = self.pool(torch.nn.functional.relu(self.conv3(x)))
        x = x.view(-1, 64 * 4 * 4)
        x = torch.nn.functional.relu(self.fc1(x))
        x = torch.nn.functional.relu(self.fc2(x))
        x = self.fc3(x)
        return torch.nn.functional.log_softmax(x, dim=1)

#    
cnn_model = ConvolutionalNeuralNetwork()

#     CPU
learning_rate = 0.1 #  
num_epochs = 10 #  

#    
device = torch.device("cpu")
cnn_model.to(device)

#     
loss_function = torch.nn.CrossEntropyLoss()

#     
optimizer = torch.optim.SGD(cnn_model.parameters(), lr = learning_rate)
print('learning rate: ', learning_rate)
print('number of epochs: ', num_epochs)
print('loss function: ', loss_function)
print('optimizer: ', optimizer)

#    top-1
def get_accuracy(data_loader, model):
    tp = 0
    n = 0
    start_time = time.time()
    with torch.no_grad():
        for images, labels in data_loader: #    
            #       
            outputs = model(images)
            _, predicted = torch.max(outputs.data, 1)
            n += labels.size(0) #  ,   batch_size
            tp += (predicted == labels).sum() #    
    mean_time = time.time() - start_time
    return tp / n, mean_time / n

training_time = time.time()
for epoch in range(num_epochs): #   
    for i, (images, labels) in enumerate(train_data_loader): #    
        #    
        images = images.requires_grad_().to(device)
        labels = labels.to(device)
        #  
        outputs = cnn_model(images) #   
        loss = loss_function(outputs, labels) #   , loss.item()  
        #  
        optimizer.zero_grad() #    
        loss.backward() #    
        optimizer.step() #   

    #         
    accuracy, mean_time = get_accuracy(train_data_loader, cnn_model)
    print('Epoch[{}]: accuracy = {}'.
        format(epoch, accuracy))
print('Training time: ', time.time() - training_time, 'seconds')
